Matariki
Homonym Number:
Word Class: noun
Sense Number:
Definition:(Te Matariki) the Pleiades, the heliacal rising of which in early winter marks the Maori New Year.
Origin: [none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain: [none]
Region: [none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: Jim writes: now an occasional celebration by urban as well as rural Maori. Known to me from posters etc. Not in DNZE.
